               <p>1695. <persName id="def1-1695-18420509" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1695-18420509" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1695-18420509" type="age" value="36"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1695-18420509" type="surname" value="HAMMERSTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1695-18420509" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM HAMMERSTON</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18420509-1695-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18420509-1695-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18420509-1695-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>for stealing, on the <rs id="t18420509-cd-239" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420509-1695-offence-1 t18420509-cd-239"></join>18th of April</rs>, 4lbs. weight of copper pipe, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18420509-name-1447" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-1447" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-1447" type="surname" value="LANGTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-1447" type="given" value="JOHN BUCKNELL"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18420509-1695-offence-1 t18420509-name-1447"></join>John Bucknell Langton</persName> and another, his masters.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420509-name-1448" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-1448" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-1448" type="surname" value="DOWNING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-1448" type="given" value="CHARLES HENRY"></interp>CHARLES HENRY DOWNING</persName>
                  </hi>. I am manager for John Bucknell Langton and another; the prisoner was employed by them. In consequence of</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184205090225"></xptr>
               <p>missing property, I directed Barker to watch—this copper pipe is my mas<lb></lb>ters'—the prisoner bad no business with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What value is it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Half-a crown—it would not be the sort of thing to mend a shoot—it could not be used to mend one—our shoots are made of tin, not copper.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420509-name-1449" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-1449" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-1449" type="surname" value="BARKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-1449" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD BARKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I was desired to watch—I watched four days behind some casks—on the 18th I saw the prisoner come and take some pipe off the press, and take it as far as the door—he put it down by the door and walked into the middle of the yard, saw it was all clear, came in, took up the pipe, and went into a stoke-hole, at one corner of the yard—I followed, and heard him beating it up with a hammer—it was quite straight when he took it—when I came in sight he put it under the furnace belonging to the steam-boiler—I thanked him for coming, as I was tired of waiting for him—he asked what I meant—I said I had been watching the copper pipe which he had taken, and asked him where it was—he said under the dust-hole, and showed me where it was—he asked me to see if I could not rub it up with his master on his behalf—I said I could not.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> He went to his work, did he not? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, and when his time was up he was taken into custody—he did not escape from the premises—he had been in the employ nearly four years.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18420509-1695-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
